Case for diagnosis: umbilical metastasis of pancreatic carcinoma (Sister Mary Joseph's Nodule). A 56-year-old man was hospitalized with a history of diffuse abdominal pain. Cutaneous examination revealed an erythematous to violaceous, infiltrative nodule of the umbilicus. Histologic examination demonstrated poorly differentiated adenocarcinoma. Abdominal tomography showed advanced pancreatic cancer with metastatic involvement of the liver and the diagnosis of pancreatic adenocarcinoma with umbilical metastasis -- Sister Mary Joseph's nodule.